radiographic_examinations.findings: Old pacemaker wires on the right side, left-sided pacemaker generator with dual leads, cardiomegaly, tortuosity of the thoracic aorta, no focal consolidation, no pneumothoraces, postoperative changes with resection of the lateral clavicle on the right, loss of subacromial space consistent with rotator cuff rupture, suture within the humeral head consistent with previous rotator cuff repair, wedging and compression deformities of a lower thoracic vertebral body, possibly T10.
